children.subject: I am currently taking 161 and 162 together and it is a good combo to take, but it looks like your second schedule will be a bit more balanced with one project heavy course and one problem set course each semester, rather than taking 2 project heavy and 2 problem set heavy courses separately.

I agree, I also think 110 is a better choice if you can only take 1 upper div math. Although if you can take two, 104 in the fall and 105 in the spring will be great -maybe even better than 110 alone.

Would recommend 110 over 104 if thats the only upper div math class you are going to be taking. 104 helps set you up for other upper div math classes but I don't think it's that valuable in in of itself.

history.content:
Hi!

I'm going to be a senior next semester, and I'm not really sure how to schedule my final two semesters. I have 3 CS classes left, and I know that I want to do 189, 161, and 162. I also really want to take one upper div math class (probably 104). I'm also potentially interested in the 5th year MS, but I don't know if how I schedule my final classes will affect my admission prospects. I'm thinking of the following two options: 

Fall 2019: 161, 162, breadth, breadth; Spring 2020: 189, 104, breadth

Fall 2019: 162, 104, breadth, breadth; Spring 2020, 189, 161, breadth

Which one do you guys think is the better option to do?
history.subject: Course Advice for Senior Year
